name: Kid's Room
description:
A small board made by small kids.
<DEFAULT>Great board for beginners!

events.SS Give Golden Mushroom:
; NAME: SS Give Golden Mushroom
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -48 ; Including 4 byte pad
SW RA 40(SP)
SW S2 36(SP)
SW S1 32(SP)
SW S0 28(SP)

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP

; Figure out which player item slots to fill
ADDU S0 R0 R0

LUI S1 hi(p1_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p2_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p2_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p3_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p3_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p4_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p4_item1)

; Figure out if the current player can even fit the item
determineslot:
ADDIU S2 R0 0xFF
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 givegolden ; First slot empty (0xFF)
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 givegolden
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 givegolden
NOP

; If we reached here, the player has too many items.
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(cannotGiveItemMsg)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(cannotGiveItemMsg)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
J exit
NOP

givegolden:
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(gotGoldenMsg)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(gotGoldenMsg)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

ADDIU S2 R0 0x0A ; Golden Mushroom value
SB S2 0(S1)

JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 R0 0x10E ; hidden block sound effect

exit:
LW RA 40(SP)
LW S2 36(SP)
LW S1 32(SP)
LW S0 28(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 48


.align 16
cannotGiveItemMsg:
.byte 0x05 ; green
.ascii "Hey "
.byte 0x08 ; white
.ascii "Come back and get this "
.byte 0x06 ; yellow
.byte 0x0A ; \n
.ascii "Golden Mushroom "
.byte 0x08 ; white
.ascii "when you have room"
.byte 0x85 ; .
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

.align 16
gotGoldenMsg:
.byte 0x05 ; green
.ascii "Hey "
.byte 0x08 ; white
.ascii "Zip through this long path "
.byte 0x0A ; \n
.ascii "with this shiny"
.byte 0x06 ; yellow
.ascii " Golden Mushroom"
.byte 0x08 ; white
.byte 0xC2 ; !
.byte 0xC2, 0x16, 0x19
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

events.Adjust Current Player Coins:
; NAME: Adjust Current Player Coins
; GAMES: MP1_USA,MP2_USA,MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Number|coins

ADDIU SP SP -4
SW RA 0(SP)

; Give the player the coins
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP
ADDIU A0 V0 0
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
ADDIU A1 R0 coins

; Display the coin change by the player stats
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP
ADDIU A0 V0 0
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
ADDIU A1 R0 coins

; Sleep for 30 frames to let coin change take effect
JAL SleepProcess
ADDIU A0 R0 30

LW RA 0(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 4

events.SS Give Random Coins in Range:
; NAME: SS Give Random Coins in Range
; GAMES: MP1_USA,MP2_USA,MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -8
SW RA 4(SP)
SW S0 0(SP)

.definelabel MAX_COINS,12

JAL guRandom ; Generates random 32-bit int
NOP
; Random int was returned in V0

divide:
ADDIU T0 R0 MAX_COINS
DIVU V0 T0 ; V0 / T0
MFHI S0 ; HI contains the remainder, pull that into S0

; Get the current player index
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP

; Give the player the coins
ADDIU A0 V0 0
ADDU A1 S0 R0
JAL AdjustPlayerCoins
NOP

; Display the coin change by the player stats
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP
ADDIU A0 V0 0
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
ADDU A1 S0 R0

; Sleep for 30 frames to let coin change take effect
JAL SleepProcess
ADDIU A0 R0 30

LW RA 4(SP)
LW S0 0(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 8

events.Coin Range Fixed:
; NAME: Coin Range Fixed
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -56 ; Including 4 byte pad
SW RA 36(SP)
SW S0 28(SP)
SW S1 0(SP)


;BEGIN MESSAGE DISPLAY CODE

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(IntroMessage)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(IntroMessage)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

; The rest here perform the "wait for confirmation"
; and probably messagebox teardown.
JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
;END MESSAGE DISPLAY CODE

.definelabel MAX_COINS,6
.definelabel MORECOINS,6

JAL 0x8000B16C ; Generates random 1-byte integer
NOP
; Random int was returned in V0

divide:
ADDIU T0 R0 MAX_COINS
DIVU V0 T0 ; V0 / T0
MFHI S1 ; HI contains the remainder, pull that into S1

; Get the current player index
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP
ADDIU A0 V0 0
ADDIU A1 S1 MORECOINS
JAL 0x800F5D44 ; Changes player's coin amount
NOP

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Value is at V0
NOP
ADDIU A0 V0 0
ADDIU A1 S1 MORECOINS
JAL 0x800E1F48 ; Displays player's coin loss on-screen
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 30
JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 30 frames
NOP


LW RA 36(SP)
LW S0 28(SP)
LW S1 0(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 56

.align 16
IntroMessage:
.ascii "You grab a few coins off the ground"
.byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
.byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
.byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
.byte 0x0A ; Enter (Writes below)
.ascii "You thief"
.byte 0x82 ; Comma (,)
.ascii " those coins do not belong to you"
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause
events.Dead-End Reverse Fix:
; NAME: Dead-End Reverse Fix
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)
SW S1 32(SP)
SW S0 28(SP) 


JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Value is at V0
NOP

BNE V0 R0 Player2Check
NOP

ADDIU S0 R0 0x00

LUI S1 hi(0x800D111F)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(0x800D111F)
SB S0 0(S1)

J exit
NOP


Player2Check:
ADDIU A0 R0 0x02 ; Is the number less than 2?
SLT S0 V0 A0
NOP

BEQ S0 R0 Player3Check 
NOP

ADDIU S0 R0 0x00

LUI S1 hi(0x800D1157)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(0x800D1157)
SB S0 0(S1)

J exit
NOP


Player3Check:
ADDIU A0 R0 0x03 ; Is the number less than 3?
SLT S0 V0 A0
NOP

BEQ S0 R0 Player4 
NOP

ADDIU S0 R0 0x00

LUI S1 hi(0x800D118F)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(0x800D118F)
SB S0 0(S1)

J exit
NOP


Player4:
ADDIU S0 R0 0x00

LUI S1 hi(0x800D11C7)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(0x800D11C7)
SB S0 0(S1)


exit:
LW S0 28(SP)
LW S1 32(SP)
LW RA 36(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 40
